.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-JOBS\-LIST" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.2.3" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-jobs\-list \- List tracked jobs discovered under the repo tree
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose jobs list [OPTIONS]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Scan the nearest git repository root, or the current directory when no git root exists, for tracked hpc\-compose submissions and list the recorded jobs.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB--disk\-usage\fR
Include recursive disk\-usage totals for tracked job paths.
.TP
\fB--tag\fR \fITAG\fR
Only list jobs carrying this tag; repeat to require every given tag.
.TP
\fB--format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format. Possible values: text, json.
.TP
\fB--color\fR \fIWHEN\fR
Controls colored output. Default: auto. Possible values: auto, always, never.
.TP
\fB--quiet\fR
Suppress progress indicators and non\-essential labels.
.TP
\fB-v\fR, \fB--verbose\fR
Increase diagnostic verbosity; repeat for debug\-level logs.
.TP
\fB--debug\fR
Enable debug\-level diagnostics (equivalent to \-vv unless RUST_LOG is set).
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--offline\fR
Forbid SSH, remote delegation, Slurm scheduler contact, submissions, allocations, and cancels.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose jobs list
hpc\-compose jobs list \-\-disk\-usage
hpc\-compose jobs list \-\-format json
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
hpc\-compose(1), hpc\-compose\-jobs(1)
